                1276
            ],
            "ignore": false,
            "order": 9,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": "This means that under the equality assumption for Eq. (6),  $N$  coded-aperture images ( $I^{(1)}, \\ldots, I^{(N)}$ ) can be derived analytically from the data observed with our imaging method ( $\\bar{I}$  and  $E^{(1,2)}, \\ldots, E^{(N-1,N)}$ ). Therefore, we can state that our imaging method is *quasi-equivalent* to the baseline coded-aperture imaging method.",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
                        198,
